searched_papers [{'title': 'Global and Local Prompts Cooperation via Optimal Transport for Federated Learning', 'abstract': ' Abstract Prompt learning in pretrained visual-language models has shown remarkable flexibility across various downstream tasks. Leveraging its inherent lightweight nature, recent research attempted to integrate the powerful pretrained models into federated learning frameworks to simultaneously reduce communication costs and promote local training on insufficient data. Despite these efforts, current federated prompt learning methods lack specialized designs to systematically address severe data heterogeneities, e.g., data distribution with both label and feature shifts involved. To address this challenge, we present Federated Prompts Cooperation via Optimal Transport (FedOTP), which introduces efficient collaborative prompt learning strategies to capture diverse category traits on a per-client basis. Specifically, for each client, we learn a global prompt to extract consensus knowledge among clients, and a local prompt to capture client-specific category characteristics. Unbalanced Optimal Transport is then employed to align local visual features with these prompts, striking a balance between global consensus and local personalization. By relaxing one of the equality constraints, FedOTP enables prompts to focus solely on the core regions of image patches. Extensive experiments on datasets with various types of heterogeneities have demonstrated that our FedOTP outperforms the state-of-the-art methods. ', 'sections': {'1 Introduction': ['PromptFL: Let federated participants cooperatively learn prompts instead of models-federated learning in age of foundation model', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data', 'pFedPrompt: Learning Personalized Prompt for Vision-Language Models in Federated Learning', 'Learning transferable visual models from natural language supervision', 'Pre-train, prompt, and predict: A systematic survey of prompting methods in natural language processing', 'An algorithm for restricted least squares regression', 'On the translocation of masses', 'Reduce communication costs and preserve privacy: Prompt tuning method in federated learning', 'FedBN: Federated Learning on Non-IID Features via Local Batch Normalization', 'Efficient model personalization in federated learning via client-specific prompt generation', 'Model-contrastive federated learning'], '2 Related Work 2.1 Personalized Federated Learning': ['FedDisco: Federated Learning with Discrepancy-Aware Collaboration', 'FedTP: Federated Learning by Transformer Personalization', 'Federated learning from pre-trained models: A contrastive learning approach', 'Federated learning of a mixture of global and local models', 'Exploiting shared representations for personalized federated learning', 'FedBN: Federated Learning on Non-IID Features via Local Batch Normalization', 'FedBABU: Towards enhanced representation for federated image classification', 'Understanding convergence and generalization in federated learning through feature learning theory', 'Federated evaluation of on-device personalization', 'Federated optimization in heterogeneous networks', 'Personalized federated learning with feature alignment and classifier collaboration', 'Partialfed: Cross-domain personalized federated learning via partial initialization', 'Federated learning with personalization layers', 'Clustered federated learning: Model-agnostic distributed multitask optimization under privacy constraints'], '2 Related Work 2.2 Prompt-based Federated Learning': ['PromptFL: Let federated participants cooperatively learn prompts instead of models-federated learning in age of foundation model', 'pFedPrompt: Learning Personalized Prompt for Vision-Language Models in Federated Learning', 'Cross-domain federated adaptive prompt tuning for clip', 'Learning transferable visual models from natural language supervision', 'Conditional prompt learning for vision-language models', 'Reduce communication costs and preserve privacy: Prompt tuning method in federated learning', 'Efficient model personalization in federated learning via client-specific prompt generation', 'FedCLIP: Fast Generalization and Personalization for CLIP in Federated Learning', 'Learning Federated Visual Prompt in Null Space for MRI Reconstruction', 'Learning to prompt for vision-language models'], '2 Related Work 2.3 Optimal Transport': ['An optimal transport approach to personalized federated learning', 'Scaling algorithms for unbalanced optimal transport problems', 'Learning with a Wasserstein loss', 'Deepjdot: Deep joint distribution optimal transport for unsupervised domain adaptation', 'OT-Filter: An Optimal Transport Filter for Learning With Noisy Labels', 'Computing all optimal partial transports', 'On the translocation of masses', 'Diagonal equivalence to matrices with prescribed row and column sums', 'A Combinatorial Algorithm for Approximating the Optimal Transport in the Parallel and MPC Settings', 'Causal optimal transport for treatment effect estimation', 'Prompt learning with optimal transport for vision-language models', 'Sinkhorn distances: Lightspeed computation of optimal transport'], '3 Preliminaries 3.1 Prompt Learning': ['Learning to prompt for vision-language models', 'Learning transferable visual models from natural language supervision'], '3 Preliminaries 3.2 Optimal Transport': ['Sinkhorn distances: Lightspeed computation of optimal transport'], '4 Methodology 4.2 Global-Local Prompt Cooperation by Unbalanced Optimal Transport': ['CSOT: Curriculum and Structure-Aware Optimal Transport for Learning with Noisy Labels', 'Iterative bregman projections for regularized transportation problems', 'An algorithm for restricted least squares regression', 'Prompt learning with optimal transport for vision-language models'], '4 Methodology 4.3 Generalization Bound': ['PromptFL: Let federated participants cooperatively learn prompts instead of models-federated learning in age of foundation model'], '5 Experiments 5.1 Experimental Setup': ['Geodesic flow kernel for unsupervised domain adaptation', 'Automated flower classification over a large number of classes', 'Federated learning with personalization layers', 'Deep residual learning for image recognition', 'Learning to prompt for vision-language models', 'Personalized Cross-Silo Federated Learning on Non-IID Data', 'Personalized federated learning using hypernetworks', 'An image is worth 16x16 words: Transformers for image recognition at scale', 'Describing textures in the wild', 'Learning generative visual models from few training examples: An incremental bayesian approach tested on 101 object categories', 'Food-101–mining discriminative components with random forests', 'Learning transferable visual models from natural language supervision', 'Fine-tuning is Fine in Federated Learning', 'FedBN: Federated Learning on Non-IID Features via Local Batch Normalization', 'Federated optimization in heterogeneous networks', 'Cats and dogs', 'Learning multiple layers of features from tiny images', 'PromptFL: Let federated participants cooperatively learn prompts instead of models-federated learning in age of foundation model', 'pFedPrompt: Learning Personalized Prompt for Vision-Language Models in Federated Learning', 'Moment matching for multi-source domain adaptation'], '5 Experiments 5.2 Performance Evaluation': ['Cats and dogs', 'pFedPrompt: Learning Personalized Prompt for Vision-Language Models in Federated Learning'], '5 Experiments 5.3 Ablation Study': ['PromptFL: Let federated participants cooperatively learn prompts instead of models-federated learning in age of foundation model']}, 'source': ['ar5iv_3', '8808801416211653744']}, {'title': 'EchoPFL: Asynchronous Personalized Federated Learning on Mobile Devices with On-Demand Staleness Control', 'abstract': ' Abstract. The rise of mobile devices with abundant sensory data and local computing capabilities has driven the trend of federated learning (FL) on these devices. And personalized FL (PFL) emerges to train specific deep models for each mobile device to address data heterogeneity and varying performance preferences. However, mobile training times vary significantly, resulting in either delay (when waiting for slower devices for aggregation) or accuracy decline (when aggregation proceeds without waiting). In response, we propose a shift towards asynchronous PFL, where the server aggregates updates as soon as they are available. Nevertheless, existing asynchronous protocols are unfit for PFL because they are devised for federated training of a single global model. They suffer from slow convergence and decreased accuracy when confronted with severe data heterogeneity prevalent in PFL. Furthermore, they often exclude slower devices for staleness control, which notably compromises accuracy when these devices possess critical personalized data. Therefore, we propose EchoPFL, a coordination mechanism for asynchronous PFL. Central to EchoPFL is to include updates from all mobile devices regardless of their latency. To cope with the inevitable staleness from slow devices, EchoPFL revisits model broadcasting. It intelligently converts the unscalable broadcast to on-demand broadcast, leveraging the asymmetrical bandwidth in wireless networks and the dynamic clustering-based PFL. Experiments show that compared to status quo approaches, EchoPFL achieves a reduction of up to 88.2% in convergence time, an improvement of up to 46% in accuracy, and a decrease of 37% in communication costs. ', 'sections': {'1. Introduction': ['Towards personalized federated learning', 'Flame: Federated learning across multi-device environments', 'Federated transfer reinforcement learning for autonomous driving', 'Learning rate optimization for federated learning exploiting over-the-air computation', 'Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition', 'The requirements, challenges, and technologies for 5G of terrestrial mobile telecommunication', 'FedSEA: A Semi-Asynchronous Federated Learning Framework for Extremely Heterogeneous Devices.', 'Fine-tuning global model via data-free knowledge distillation for non-iid federated learning', 'Parameterized knowledge transfer for personalized federated learning', 'Anarchic federated learning', 'Heterofl: Computation and communication efficient federated learning for heterogeneous clients', 'SAFA: A semi-asynchronous protocol for fast federated learning with low overhead', 'Personalized federated learning with theoretical guarantees: A model-agnostic meta-learning approach', 'Client selection for federated learning with heterogeneous resources in mobile edge', 'Flower: A friendly federated learning research framework.', 'Federated multi-task learning', 'Billion-scale federated learning on mobile clients: A submodel design with tunable privacy', 'Asynchronous federated optimization', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data', 'pFL-bench: A comprehensive benchmark for personalized federated learning'], '2. Motivation and Challenge 2.1. Motivation for Asynchronous Personalized FL': ['A public domain dataset for human activity recognition using smartphones.', 'Learning multiple layers of features from tiny images', 'Towards personalized federated learning', 'Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data', 'Adaface: Quality adaptive margin for face recognition', 'Sport-related human activity detection and recognition using a smartwatch', 'Smart webcam cover: exploring the design of an intelligent webcam cover to improve usability and trust', 'GCHAR: An efficient Group-based Context—Aware human activity recognition on smartphone', 'A systematic review of smartphone-based human activity recognition methods for health research', 'Asynchronous federated optimization'], '2. Motivation and Challenge 2.2. Challenges in Asynchronous PFL with Mobile Devices': ['Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition', 'SAFA: A semi-asynchronous protocol for fast federated learning with low overhead', 'Asynchronous federated optimization', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data'], '3. Solution Overview': ['Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition'], '4. Data-aware Dynamic Clustering 4.1. Primer on Mobile Client Clustering': ['Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition'], '4. Data-aware Dynamic Clustering 4.2. On-arrival Initial Cluster Assignment of Mobile Devices': ['Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition', 'Density-based clustering over an evolving data stream with noise'], '4. Data-aware Dynamic Clustering 4.3. Feedback-aware Mobile Cluster Refinement': ['Fine-tuning global model via data-free knowledge distillation for non-iid federated learning', 'Improved fine-tuning by better leveraging pre-training data', 'Midas: Microcluster-based detector of anomalies in edge streams'], '5. In-cluster model broadcast 5.1. Advantages of In-cluster Model Broadcast': ['FedSEA: A Semi-Asynchronous Federated Learning Framework for Extremely Heterogeneous Devices.', 'Sharper convergence guarantees for asynchronous sgd for distributed and federated learning', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data'], '5. In-cluster model broadcast 5.2. Online In-cluster broadcast Frequency Prediction': ['Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data'], '7. Experiment 7.1. Experiment Setup': ['A public domain dataset for human activity recognition using smartphones.', 'Learning multiple layers of features from tiny images', 'Oort: Efficient Federated Learning via Guided Participant Selection.', 'Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data', 'FedSEA: A Semi-Asynchronous Federated Learning Framework for Extremely Heterogeneous Devices.', 'UbiEar: Bringing location-independent sound awareness to the hard-of-hearing people with smartphones', 'Asynchronous federated optimization', 'Passive Vital Sign Monitoring via Facial Vibrations Leveraging AR/VR Headsets'], '7. Experiment 7.2. Performance Comparison': ['Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition'], '8. Related Work': ['Towards personalized federated learning', 'Oort: Efficient Federated Learning via Guided Participant Selection.', 'Distreal: Distributed resource-aware learning in heterogeneous systems', 'Federated transfer reinforcement learning for autonomous driving', 'Lifelong federated reinforcement learning: a learning architecture for navigation in cloud robotic systems', 'PyramidFL: A fine-grained client selection framework for efficient federated learning', 'Clusterfl: a similarity-aware federated learning system for human activity recognition', 'Fedftha: a fine-tuning and head aggregation method in federated learning', 'FedSEA: A Semi-Asynchronous Federated Learning Framework for Extremely Heterogeneous Devices.', 'Fine-tuning global model via data-free knowledge distillation for non-iid federated learning', 'Federated learning under distributed concept drift', 'SAFA: A semi-asynchronous protocol for fast federated learning with low overhead', 'Personalized federated learning with theoretical guarantees: A model-agnostic meta-learning approach', 'Federated learning of a mixture of global and local models', 'Flower: A friendly federated learning research framework.', 'Federated multi-task learning', 'Towards Bias Correction of FedAvg over Nonuniform and Time-Varying Communications', 'Billion-scale federated learning on mobile clients: A submodel design with tunable privacy', 'Asynchronous federated optimization', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data', 'Fedmd: Heterogenous federated learning via model distillation', 'An efficient framework for clustered federated learning', 'Federated Learning for Computationally-Constrained Heterogeneous Devices: A Survey', 'GCHAR: An efficient Group-based Context—Aware human activity recognition on smartphone']}, 'source': ['ar5iv_2', '7768264510038885859']}, {'title': 'Personalization Disentanglement for Federated Learning: An explainable perspective', 'abstract': ' Abstract Personalized federated learning (PFL) jointly trains a variety of local models through balancing between knowledge sharing across clients and model personalization per client. This paper addresses PFL via explicit disentangling latent representations into two parts to capture the shared knowledge and client-specific personalization, which leads to more reliable and effective PFL. The disentanglement is achieved by a novel Federated Dual Variational Autoencoder (FedDVA), which employs two encoders to infer the two types of representations. FedDVA can produce a better understanding of the trade-off between global knowledge sharing and local personalization in PFL. Moreover, it can be integrated with existing FL methods and turn them into personalized models for heterogeneous downstream tasks. Extensive experiments validate the advantages caused by disentanglement and show that models trained with disentangled representations substantially outperform those vanilla methods. ', 'sections': {'I Introduction': ['Three approaches for personalization with applications to federated learning', 'Federated optimization in heterogeneous networks', 'Ensemble distillation for robust model fusion in federated learning', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data'], 'II Related Work': ['Personalized federated learning using hypernetworks', 'Personalized federated learning: A meta-learning approach', 'Representation learning: A review and new perspectives', 'Challenging common assumptions in the unsupervised learning of disentangled representations', 'Temporal difference variational auto-encoder', 'Fine-tuning is fine in federated learning', 'Ditto: Fair and robust federated learning through personalization', 'Model-agnostic meta-learning for fast adaptation of deep networks'], 'III Personalization Disentanglement for Federated Learning III-A Background and Notation': ['Auto-encoding variational bayes'], 'III Personalization Disentanglement for Federated Learning III-B Methodology': ['Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data'], 'V Experiment V-B Personalized Classification': ['Fine-tuning is fine in federated learning', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data', 'Ditto: Fair and robust federated learning through personalization']}, 'source': ['ar5iv_1', '8148826656532763446']}, {'title': '1 Introduction', 'abstract': '', 'sections': {}, 'source': ['ar5iv_3', '5834284827708896004']}, {'title': 'Layer-wised Model Aggregation for Personalized Federated Learning', 'abstract': ' Abstract Personalized Federated Learning (pFL) not only can capture the common priors from broad range of distributed data, but also support customized models for heterogeneous clients. Researches over the past few years have applied the weighted aggregation manner to produce personalized models, where the weights are determined by calibrating the distance of the entire model parameters or loss values, and have yet to consider the layer-level impacts to the aggregation process, leading to lagged model convergence and inadequate personalization over non-IID datasets. In this paper, we propose a novel pFL training framework dubbed Layer-wised Personalized Federated learning (pFedLA) that can discern the importance of each layer from different clients, and thus is able to optimize the personalized model aggregation for clients with heterogeneous data. Specifically, we employ a dedicated hypernetwork per client on the server side, which is trained to identify the mutual contribution factors at layer granularity. Meanwhile, a parameterized mechanism is introduced to update the layer-wised aggregation weights to progressively exploit the inter-user similarity and realize accurate model personalization. Extensive experiments are conducted over different models and learning tasks, and we show that the proposed methods achieve significantly higher performance than state-of-the-art pFL methods.  ', 'sections': {'1 Introduction': ['Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data', 'Lower bounds and optimal algorithms for personalized federated learning', 'The non-iid data quagmire of decentralized machine learning', 'Exploiting shared representations for personalized federated learning', 'Attention-mechanism-containing neural networks for high-resolution remote sensing image classification', 'Personalized federated learning with first order model optimization', 'Personalized federated learning with theoretical guarantees: A model-agnostic meta-learning approach', 'Communication-efficient on-device machine learning: Federated distillation and augmentation under non-iid private data', 'Ditto: Fair and robust federated learning through personalization', 'Federated optimization in heterogeneous networks'], '2 Related Work 2.1 Personalized Federated Learning': ['Towards personalized federated learning', 'Personalized federated learning with moreau envelopes', 'Federated user representation learning', 'Communication-efficient learning of deep networks from decentralized data', 'Parameterized knowledge transfer for personalized federated learning', 'Three approaches for personalization with applications to federated learning', 'Personalized federated learning with first order model optimization', 'Personalized federated learning with theoretical guarantees: A model-agnostic meta-learning approach', 'Communication-efficient on-device machine learning: Federated distillation and augmentation under non-iid private data', 'Federated learning with non-iid data', 'Optimizing federated learning on non-iid data with reinforcement learning', 'Personalized cross-silo federated learning on non-iid data', 'Federated multi-task learning', 'Federated evaluation of on-device personalization'], '2 Related Work 2.2 Hypernetworks': ['Continual learning with hypernetworks', 'Personalized federated learning using hypernetworks', 'Deep meta functionals for shape representation', 'Dynamic filter networks', 'Meta-learning via hypernetworks', 'Hypernetworks', 'Language modeling with recurrent highway hypernetworks', 'Smash: one-shot model architecture search through hypernetworks', 'Stochastic hyperparameter optimization through hypernetworks'], '3 Method 3.2 pFedLA Algorithm': ['Personalized cross-silo federated learning on non-iid data'], '3 Method 3.3 HeurpFedLA: Heuristic Improvement of pFedLA on Communication Efficiency': ['Fedbn: Federated learning on non-iid features via local batch normalization', 'Exploiting shared representations for personalized federated learning', 'Think locally, act globally: Federated learning with local and global representations'], '4 Evaluation 4.1 Experimental Setup': ['Fedbn: Federated learning on non-iid features via local batch normalization', 'Personalized federated learning using hypernetworks', 'Personalized federated learning with first order model optimization'], '4 Evaluation 4.4 Analysis of Communication Efficiency': ['Exploiting shared representations for personalized federated learning']}, 'source': ['ar5iv_2', '7510039614319891066']}]
